# kimi-room · env example
#
# The default deployment requires no environment variables. kimi-room is a
# self-contained interface layer: storage is in-browser (IndexedDB), and chat
# uses bring-your-own-credentials (endpoint + key set in the in-app Settings —
# an official subscription or any OpenAI-compatible endpoint). None of the below
# is required for that.
#
# The variables below apply only to the optional "core" backend — redirecting
# memory to a running kimi-core (https://github.com/marikagura/kimi-core). See
# docs/BACKENDS.md for details.

# ─── build mode ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_MODE=kimi-room        # kimi-room | kimi-airp (default kimi-room)

# ─── backend mode ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# "local" (default) = pure local + BYO chat. "core" = redirect memory to kimi-core.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_BACKEND=core

# ─── core backend (only when NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_BACKEND=core) ───────────────────
# Your running kimi-core gateway. The browser never sees the key — the
# /api/core route forwards calls server-side with this Bearer token.
# KIMI_CORE_URL=https://your-kimi-core.example.com
# KIMI_API_KEY=kimi-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Legacy alias (still read by the kimi.ts stub); KIMI_CORE_URL is preferred.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_GATEWAY=https://your-kimi-core.example.com

# ─── persistent adapter (optional · server persistence) ──────────────────────
# Where the structured dashboard (calendar / sleep / keepsakes / memory …) lives.
# Default "idb" = in-browser IndexedDB, zero config. The two server options below
# move it onto your own DB so it survives a browser wipe and syncs across devices.
# Full setup (schema + RLS / owner login + deploy) is in docs/SELF-HOST.md.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_ADAPTER=supabase      # idb (default) | supabase | prisma | core

# supabase adapter — browser-direct + Row-Level Security. Run supabase/schema.sql
# once, then use the project's ANON (publishable) key here, never service_role.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=YOUR-ANON-PUBLISHABLE-KEY

# prisma adapter — server /api/store over any Postgres. Install @prisma/client +
# prisma (see docs/SELF-HOST.md), then set:
# DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:5432/dbname
# KIMI_OWNER_PASSWORD=choose-a-strong-owner-password
# KIMI_SESSION_SECRET=optional-random-string-to-salt-the-session-cookie

# core adapter — store dashboard data in a running kimi-core (the SAME backend as
# memory/RAG). Set NEXT_PUBLIC_KIMI_ADAPTER=core and reuse the core backend vars
# above (KIMI_CORE_URL + KIMI_API_KEY); enable the store extension on kimi-core
# (KIMI_EXTENSIONS=store). See docs/SELF-HOST.md.
